31/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Interior Minister Dusan Mihajlovic says he will resign if allegations against him are proved true in court.
He was responding to accusations by deputy head of G17 Plus and former Central Bank Governor Mladjan Dinkic who says Mihajlovic arranged for his company to win an IBM software contract for the interior ministry.
In other news, three people were injured in Belgrade on Thursday (30 October) when police moved in to prevent demonstrators from entering parliament.
A scuffle broke out when trade union members tried to interrupt debate on a no-confidence vote for the Serbian government.
Several thousand workers had been rallying for two days to coincide with the debate.
(B92, BBC, Beta, AFP - 30/10/03)
